<span id="freeTextContainer7187662084744336530">&quot;You have to tame the horse before you can let it have its head.&quot; <br/>~Mazor Rackham p. 50<br/><br/>&quot;&apos;Who are you writing to?&apos;<br/>&apos;Whom. You foreigners are wrecking the English language.&apos;<br/>&apos;I&apos;m not speaking English. I&apos;m speaking Common. There&apos;s no &apos;whom&apos; in Common.&apos;&quot;<br/>~Mrs. Wiggin and Bean p. 104<br/><br/>&quot;&apos;Why do you always drink that stuff?&apos; asked John Paul<br/>Peter looked surprised. &apos;Guarana? it&apos;s my duty as an American to never drink Coke or Pepsi in a country that has an indigenous soft drink. Besides which, I like it.&apos;<br/>&apos;It&apos;s </span>
